    "updated_at": "2023-06-24T11:29:08Z",
    "body": "Yes exactly, I've encountered the problem using these instructions: \r\n\r\n> Add the following to the end of your Nushell env file (find it by running $nu.env-path in Nushell):\r\n> \r\n> `mkdir ~/.cache/starship`\r\n> `starship init nu | save -f ~/.cache/starship/init.nu`\r\n> And add the following to the end of your Nushell configuration (find it by running $nu.config-path):\r\n> \r\n> `use ~/.cache/starship/init.nu`\r\n\r\nI am new to nushell so I wasn't aware that they had source as an option too. This solves the issue much more elegantly. \r\n\r\nThe issue now is a mismatch between the behaviour of `starship init nu` and the documentation in the Readme on the master-branch. Either the readme should state to use `source` instead of `use` or `starship init nu` should wrap the file in an `export-env` context.",
