    "updated_at": "2023-07-06T20:29:49Z",
    "body": "> The issue now is a mismatch between the behaviour of `starship init nu` and the documentation in the Readme on the master-branch. Either the readme should state to use `source` instead of `use` or `starship init nu` should wrap the file in an `export-env` context.\n\nThis will be resolved when we release the next version of starship. The readme and all the other documentation in the repo is only reliable with the code at the same revision, for example the readme on the master branch is only really reliable if you use starship that has been built from the master branch. I would recommend using [starship.rs](https://starship.rs) as that is kept in sync with the latest release of starship. ",
